-- Semapa to Invest About 300 Million Euros in Brazil, Diario Says
-- B y   H e n r i q u e   A l m e i d a
-- 2012-03-19T08:32:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-19/semapa-to-invest-about-300-million-euros-in-brazil-diario-says.html
Semapa-Sociedade de Investimento e
Gestao SGPS SA , a Portuguese holding company that controls
cement maker Secil, will invest about 300 million euros ($394
million) in  Brazil ’s cement industry,  Diario Economico  reported,
citing the prospectus of Semapa’s bond sale.  Semapa will invest about 240 million euros in a new plant
in Brazil after it agreed to buy a 50 percent stake in Supremo
Cimento SA, the Portuguese newspaper said, citing the document
for the planned sale of as much as 150 million euros of Semapa
bonds.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Henrique Almeida in Lisbon at 
 halmeida5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
